H0.text: Melting ice is not an example of a chemical change.

H1.text: Corroding silver is not an example of a chemical change.

H2.text: Burning match is NOT an example of a chemical change.

H3.text: Rotting vegetation is not an example of a chemical change.

A4.text: Melting is a physical process that results in the phase transition of a substance from a solid to a liquid.
